49 Body brownish, usually with red, black, green, golden or purple blotches; distance between both dorsal fins less than the length of the base of the first dorsal fin; pelvic fin in an anterior position, its origin located below or very close to the origin of the pectoral fins in the vertical plane; caudal fin rounded or convex (
